'''Glen Mortimer''' is an Australian former professional [[rugby league]] footballer who played for [[Cronulla-Sutherland Sharks|Cronulla-Sutherland]]. He is also the brother to [[Chris Mortimer]], [[Peter Mortimer (rugby league)|Peter Mortimer]] and [[Steve Mortimer]].  The brothers were all raised in the [[Riverina]] city of [[Wagga Wagga, New South Wales]].<ref name="brothers">{{cite web
| url = http://www.wagga.nsw.gov.au/www/html/1265-mortimer-steve.asp?intSiteID=1
| title = MORTIMERS
| work = Museum of the Riverina - Sporting Hall of Fame
| publisher = [[City of Wagga Wagga]]
| accessdate = 2007-09-17
}}</ref>

He started in the lower grades at [[Canterbury-Bankstown Bulldogs|Canterbury-Bankstown]] before moving to [[Cronulla-Sutherland Sharks|Cronulla-Sutherland]].

